e crammed in together; Harry could not comfortably sit, but crouched, his knees jutting over the edge of the boat, which began to move at once. There was no sound other than the silken rustle of the boat\rquote 
s prow cleaving the water; it moved without their he
lp, as though an invisible rope were pulling it onwards towards the light in the centre. Soon they could no longer see the walls of the cavern; they might have been at sea except that there were no waves.
\par Harry looked down and saw the reflected gold of his wand-light sparkling and glittering on the black water as they passed. The boat was carving deep ripples upon the glassy surface, grooves in the dark mirror ...
\par And then Harry saw it, marble-white, floating inches below the surface.
\par \lquote Professor!\rquote  he said, and his startled voice echoed loudly over the silent water.
\par \lquote Harry?\rquote 
